history.content: I'm not certain.  If additional space is created in the CS section, students waitlisted for that section will have first shot.  Luckily, there really aren't very many conceivable scenarios where which department listing for the same course was on your transcript would have any negative(or positive)  impact.

Is it possible to enroll in Stats C8 so that I can get into the class and then switch to CS C8 so that my transcript says CS C8? 

It seems like there are 44 people on the waitlist with 160 people in that class so I don't think I'll be able to enroll in CS C8 during adjustment period whereas I can enroll in Information C8 or Stats C8. 

Bottom line question is: is it possible to enroll in a crosslisted section that isn't CS c8, and have the option to get CS c8 marked on my trasncript?
history.subject: CS C8 (Data Science) Course Expansion
